[36m│[0m # Repository Guidelines                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Repository Purpose                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m OpenHands CLI is a standalone execute_powershell interface (Textual TUI)    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m for interacting with the OpenHands agent.                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This repo contains the current CLI UX, including the Textual TUI and a      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m browser-served view via `openhands web`.                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### References                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent-sdk example:                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m https://github.com/All-Hands-AI/agent-sdk/blob/main/examples/hello_world.py [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - If you need to compare with upstream OpenHands code, use `$GITHUB_TOKEN`  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m for access.                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Project Structure & Module Organization                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `openhands_cli/`: Core CLI/TUI code (`openhands_cli/entrypoint.py`,       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `openhands_cli/tui/`, `openhands_cli/auth/`, `openhands_cli/mcp/`,          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `openhands_cli/cloud/`, `openhands_cli/user_actions/`,                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `openhands_cli/conversations/`, `openhands_cli/theme.py`, helpers in        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `openhands_cli/utils.py`). Keep new modules snake_case and colocate tests.  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `tests/`: Pytest suite covering units, integration, and snapshot tests;   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m mirrors source layout. `tui_e2e/`: tests for the PyInstaller-built          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m executable.                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `scripts/acp/`: JSON-RPC and debug helpers for ACP development; `hooks/`: [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m PyInstaller/runtime hooks.                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Tooling & packaging: `Makefile` for common tasks, `build.sh`/`build.py`   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m for PyInstaller artifacts, `openhands-cli.spec` for the frozen binary,      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `uv.lock` for resolved deps.                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `.agents/skills/`: agent guidance for this repo.                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Setup, Build, and Development Commands                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This repository uses **uv** for dependency management and running tooling   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m (such as in `Makefile`, CI workflows, and `uv.lock`). Use `uv` 0.11.6 or    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m newer for local development; older versions can serialize `uv.lock`         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m differently around relative `exclude-newer`. Avoid using `pip install ...`  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m directly if possible.                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - minimum supported `uv` version: `0.11.6`                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - install dependencies: `make install` (runs `uv sync`)                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - install dev dependencies: `make install-dev` (runs `uv sync --group dev`) [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - install pre-commit hooks: `uv run pre-commit install` (included in `make  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m build`)                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - build (sync + install hooks): `make build`                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - lint (all pre-commit hooks): `make lint`                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - format: `make format`                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run the Textual TUI (interactive; prefer running inside tmux so you can   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m detach with `Ctrl+b d`): `make run` (or `uv run openhands`)                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run the Textual TUI (automation-friendly; use for agent-driven runs): `uv [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m run openhands --exit-without-confirmation` (quit with `Ctrl+Q`; `Ctrl+C`    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m does not work once the TUI is running)                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **fast TUI development** (see [Fast TUI Development                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Workflow](#fast-tui-development-workflow) below):                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   - `make run-watch` - Auto-restart on file changes (recommended for most   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m development)                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run the browser-served web app (Textual `textual-serve`): `openhands web` [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run the Docker-based OpenHands GUI server: `openhands serve`              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run the ACP entrypoint: `uv run openhands-acp`                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run unit/integration tests: `make test` (for faster runs: `uv run pytest  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m -m "not integration" --ignore=tests/snapshots`)                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run snapshot tests (Textual UI): `make test-snapshots` (or `uv run pytest [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m tests/snapshots -v`; use `--snapshot-update` when updating snapshots)       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run binary tests: `make test-binary` (or `uv run pytest tui_e2e`)         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - run unit/integration + snapshot tests together: `make test-all`           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - build PyInstaller binaries: `./build.sh --install-pyinstaller`            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Development Guidelines                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Fast TUI Development Workflow                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #### Auto-restart on file changes (recommended)                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The fastest way to iterate on TUI changes:                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m make run-watch                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This watches `openhands_cli/` and automatically restarts the app when you   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m save any `.py` or `.tcss` file. Just edit, save, and see your changes.      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Linting Requirements                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Before any commit, run `make lint` and only commit after it passes.** Use [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `make lint` to run all pre-commit hooks on all files, and do it before      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m every commit (not after) to avoid CI failures.                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Typing Requirements                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Prefer modern typing syntax (`X | None` over `Optional[X]`) in new code.    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Documentation Guidelines                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Don’t add new root-level `.md` files or “summary updates” to `README.md`  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m unless explicitly requested (use this `AGENTS.md` for repo guidance).       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Coding Style & Naming Conventions                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Python 3.12, ruff formatting (88-char line limit, double quotes).         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Ruff enforced rules: pycodestyle, pyflakes, isort, pyupgrade, unused-arg  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m checks (tests allow fixture-style args), and guards against mutable         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m defaults.                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Keep modules/dirs snake_case; classes in CapWords; user-facing            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m commands/flags kebab-case as in existing entrypoints.                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Type checking via `pyright` (`uv run pyright`); prefer type hints on new  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m functions and public interfaces.                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Testing Guidelines                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Unit/integration tests live under `tests/` (excluding `tests/snapshots`)  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and run via `make test`.                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Snapshot tests live under `tests/snapshots/` and run via `make            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m test-snapshots`.                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Binary tests live under `tui_e2e/` and run via `make test-binary`.        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Pytest discovery: files `test_*.py`, classes `Test*`, functions `test_*`. [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use `@pytest.mark.integration` for costly flows.                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Match test locations to implementation (`tests/` mirrors                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `openhands_cli/`); add fixtures in `tests/conftest.py` when shared.         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Run `make test` before PRs; run snapshot/binary tests when relevant to    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the change.                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Binary Tests with Mock LLM                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Binary tests in `tui_e2e/` can use `mock_llm_server.py` for deterministic [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m testing without real LLM calls.                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - The mock LLM server provides OpenAI-compatible endpoints with proper tool [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m call format.                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Use `openai/gpt-4o-mock` as the model name (litellm requires a provider   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m prefix).                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Snapshot Testing with pytest-textual-snapshot                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The CLI uses                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [pytest-textual-snapshot](https://github.com/Textualize/pytest-textual-snap [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m shot) for visual regression testing of Textual UI components. Snapshots are [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m SVG screenshots that capture the exact visual state of the application.     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Running Snapshot Tests                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Run all snapshot tests                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m make test-snapshots                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # or: uv run pytest tests/snapshots/ -v                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Update snapshots when intentional UI changes are made                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m uv run pytest tests/snapshots/ --snapshot-update                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Snapshot Test Location                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Test files**: `tests/snapshots/test_app_snapshots.py`,                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `tests/snapshots/test_visualizer_snapshots.py`                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Generated snapshots**:                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `tests/snapshots/__snapshots__/test_app_snapshots/*.svg`,                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `tests/snapshots/__snapshots__/test_visualizer_snapshots/*.svg`             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `tests/tui/widgets/test_richlog_visualizer.py` is the primary unit test   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m suite for `richlog_visualizer.py`; for maintainability refactors there,     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m prefer targeted unit coverage in that file plus snapshot tests only when    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m rendered output changes visually.                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Writing Snapshot Tests                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Snapshot tests must be **synchronous** (not async). The `snap_compare`      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fixture handles async internally:                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m from textual.app import App, ComposeResult                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m from textual.widgets import Static, Footer                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m def test_my_widget(snap_compare):                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     """Snapshot test for my widget."""                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     class MyTestApp(App):                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             yield Static("Content")                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             yield Footer()                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     assert snap_compare(MyTestApp(), terminal_size=(80, 24))                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #### Using `run_before` for Setup                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m To interact with the app before taking a screenshot:                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m def test_with_interaction(snap_compare):                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     class MyApp(App):                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             yield InputField(id="input")                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     async def setup(pilot):                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         input_field = pilot.app.query_one(InputField)                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         input_field.input_widget.value = "Hello!"                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         await pilot.pause()                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     assert snap_compare(MyApp(), terminal_size=(80, 24), run_before=setup)  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #### Using `press` for Key Simulation                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m def test_with_focus(snap_compare):                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     assert snap_compare(                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         MyApp(),                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         terminal_size=(80, 24),                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         press=["tab", "tab"],  # Press tab twice to move focus              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     )                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Viewing Snapshots Visually                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m To view the generated SVG snapshots in a browser:                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Start a local HTTP server** in the snapshots directory:                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```powershell                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    cd tests/snapshots/__snapshots__/test_app_snapshots                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    python -m http.server 12000                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Open in browser** using the work host URL:                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    https://work-1-<id>.prod-runtime.all-hands.dev/<snapshot-name>.svg       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    Example snapshot names:                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - `TestExitModalSnapshots.test_exit_modal_initial_state.svg`             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - `TestVisualizerSnapshots.test_multiple_actions_alignment.svg`          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Stop the server** when done:                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```powershell                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    pkill -f "python -m http.server 12000"                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Snapshot Best Practices                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Mock external dependencies so snapshots are deterministic.                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Always pass a fixed `terminal_size=(width, height)`.                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Commit SVG snapshots.                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Review snapshot diffs carefully.                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Commit & Pull Request Guidelines                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Follow the repo’s pattern: `<scope>: <concise message> (#NNN)` (see `git  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m log`), where scope is the touched area (e.g., `auth`, `tui`, `fix`).        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Keep commits focused; include tests and formatting in the same change     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m when practical.                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - PRs should describe behavior changes, list key commands run (e.g.,        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m tests/build), link related issues, and include before/after notes or        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m screenshots for UI/TUI updates.                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Check in `uv.lock` changes when dependency versions move; avoid           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m committing secrets or local config.                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Contribution standards (agents-first)                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Keep PRs minimally scoped; prefer multiple PRs over one large PR when it  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m reduces risk and review load.                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Include tests for behavior changes (unit/integration/e2e as appropriate). [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If you can’t add tests, explain why and what manual verification you        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m performed.                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - For UI/TUI changes, snapshot tests are the preferred evidence. If         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m snapshots aren't available/appropriate, include screenshots (and note the   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m execute_powershell size used).                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Before opening a PR, run this verification flow (and include the exact    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m commands run in the PR description):                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   1. `make lint`                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   2. `make test`                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   3. If you touched ACP / binary executable code (e.g., `tui_e2e/`,         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `openhands_cli/acp_impl/`, `openhands_cli/mcp/`, auth/connection flow):     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `make test-binary`                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   4. If you touched TUI code (e.g., `openhands_cli/tui/`, widgets, styles,  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m layout): `make test-snapshots` (use `--snapshot-update` only for            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m intentional UI changes)                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #### PR submission checklist                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Scope is minimal and focused on one change                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Tests added/updated for behavior changes (or PR explains why not)     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] `make lint`                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] `make test`                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] (If ACP/binary executable touched) `make test-binary`                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] (If TUI touched) `make test-snapshots` run and snapshots              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m updated/reviewed                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] PR description includes: what changed, why, commands run, and UI      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m evidence (snapshots/screenshots)                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Security & Configuration Tips                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Do not embed API keys or endpoints in code; rely on runtime               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m configuration/env vars when integrating new services.                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - When packaging, verify no sensitive files are included in `dist/`; adjust [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `openhands-cli.spec` if new assets are added.                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## TUI State Management Architecture                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The TUI uses a reactive state management pattern with clear separation of   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m concerns. Key files are in `openhands_cli/tui/core/`.                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Core Components                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **ConversationContainer (`state.py`)** - Reactive state holder              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - A Textual `Container` widget that owns all conversation-related reactive  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m properties                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Properties include: `running`, `conversation_id`, `conversation_title`,   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `confirmation_policy`, `pending_action_count`, `elapsed_seconds`, `metrics` [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - UI widgets bind to these properties via `data_bind()` and auto-update     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m when state changes                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Provides thread-safe state update methods (e.g., `set_running()`,         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `set_conversation_id()`)                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Composes the main UI hierarchy: `ScrollableContent` +                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `InputAreaContainer`                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **ConversationManager (`conversation_manager.py`)** - Message router        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - A thin Textual `Container` that listens to messages and delegates to      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m controllers                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Owns: `RunnerRegistry`, `ConfirmationPolicyService`, and all controllers  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Message handlers (`@on(MessageType)`) route to appropriate controllers    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Provides public API methods that post messages internally                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Controllers** - Single-responsibility business logic                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `UserMessageController` - Handles user input, renders messages,           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m queues/processes with runner                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `ConversationCrudController` - Creates new conversations, resets state    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `ConversationSwitchController` - Orchestrates switching (pause current,   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m prepare new)                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `ConfirmationFlowController` - Shows confirmation panel, handles user     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m decisions                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **RunnerFactory + RunnerRegistry** - Runner lifecycle                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `RunnerFactory` - Creates `ConversationRunner` instances with             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m dependencies                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `RunnerRegistry` - Caches runners by conversation_id, tracks current      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m runner                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Widget Hierarchy                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m OpenHandsApp                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m └── ConversationManager(Container)  ← message router                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     └── ConversationContainer(#conversation_state)  ← reactive state        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         ├── ScrollableContent(#scroll_view)  ← binds to conversation_id,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m pending_action_count                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         │   ├── SplashContent(#splash_content)  ← binds to conversation_id  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         │   └── ... dynamically added conversation widgets                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         └── InputAreaContainer(#input_area)  ← handles slash commands       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             ├── WorkingStatusLine  ← binds to running, elapsed_seconds      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             ├── InputField  ← binds to conversation_id,                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m pending_action_count                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             └── InfoStatusLine  ← binds to running, metrics                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Data Flow                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **User input** → `InputField` posts `UserInputSubmitted` → bubbles to    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `ConversationManager` → `UserMessageController.handle_user_message()`       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Slash commands** → `InputField` posts `SlashCommandSubmitted` →        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `InputAreaContainer` routes to command handlers → posts operation messages  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m (e.g., `CreateConversation`)                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **State changes** → Controllers call `ConversationContainer.set_*()`     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m methods → reactive properties update → bound widgets auto-refresh           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Cross-thread updates** → `ConversationContainer._schedule_update()`    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m uses `call_from_thread()` for thread safety                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Key Design Principles                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Reactive state**: UI components bind to `ConversationContainer`         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m properties via `data_bind()`, auto-update on changes                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Single source of truth**: `ConversationContainer` owns all conversation [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m state                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Thread safety**: State updates use `call_from_thread()` when called     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m from background threads                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Message-based communication**: Components communicate via Textual       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m messages that bubble up the widget tree                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Controller pattern**: Business logic split into focused controllers,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `ConversationManager` is just a router                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [BEGIN context from                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [superpowers/brainstorming/spec-document-reviewer-prompt]]                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Spec Document Reviewer Prompt Template                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use this template when dispatching a spec document reviewer subagent.       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Purpose:** Verify the spec is complete, consistent, and ready for         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m implementation planning.                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Dispatch after:** Spec document is written to docs/superpowers/specs/     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Task tool (general-purpose):                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   description: "Review spec document"                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   prompt: |                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     You are a spec document reviewer. Verify this spec is complete and      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ready for planning.                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Spec to review:** [SPEC_FILE_PATH]                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## What to Check                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     | Category | What to Look For |                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     |----------|------------------|                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     | Completeness | TODOs, placeholders, "TBD", incomplete sections |      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     | Consistency | Internal contradictions, conflicting requirements |     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     | Clarity | Requirements ambiguous enough to cause someone to build the [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m wrong thing |                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     | Scope | Focused enough for a single plan — not covering multiple      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m independent subsystems |                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     | YAGNI | Unrequested features, over-engineering |                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## Calibration                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Only flag issues that would cause real problems during implementation [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m planning.**                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     A missing section, a contradiction, or a requirement so ambiguous it    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m could be                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     interpreted two different ways — those are issues. Minor wording        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m improvements,                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     stylistic preferences, and "sections less detailed than others" are     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m not.                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     Approve unless there are serious gaps that would lead to a flawed plan. [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## Output Format                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## Spec Review                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Status:** Approved | Issues Found                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Issues (if any):**                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - [Section X]: [specific issue] - [why it matters for planning]         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Recommendations (advisory, do not block approval):**                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - [suggestions for improvement]                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Reviewer returns:** Status, Issues (if any), Recommendations              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [BEGIN context from [superpowers/brainstorming/visual-companion]]           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Visual Companion Guide                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Browser-based visual brainstorming companion for showing mockups, diagrams, [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and options.                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## When to Use                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Decide per-question, not per-session. The test: **would the user understand [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m this better by seeing it than reading it?**                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Use the browser** when the content itself is visual:                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **UI mockups** — wireframes, layouts, navigation structures, component    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m designs                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Architecture diagrams** — system components, data flow, relationship    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m maps                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Side-by-side visual comparisons** — comparing two layouts, two color    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m schemes, two design directions                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Design polish** — when the question is about look and feel, spacing,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m visual hierarchy                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Spatial relationships** — state machines, flowcharts, entity            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m relationships rendered as diagrams                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Use the execute_powershell** when the content is text or tabular:         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Requirements and scope questions** — "what does X mean?", "which        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m features are in scope?"                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Conceptual A/B/C choices** — picking between approaches described in    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m words                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Tradeoff lists** — pros/cons, comparison tables                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Technical decisions** — API design, data modeling, architectural        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m approach selection                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Clarifying questions** — anything where the answer is words, not a      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m visual preference                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m A question *about* a UI topic is not automatically a visual question. "What [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m kind of wizard do you want?" is conceptual — use the execute_powershell.    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "Which of these wizard layouts feels right?" is visual — use the browser.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## How It Works                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The server watches a directory for HTML files and serves the newest one to  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the browser. You write HTML content to `screen_dir`, the user sees it in    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m their browser and can click to select options. Selections are recorded to   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `state_dir/events` that you read on your next turn.                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Content fragments vs full documents:** If your HTML file starts with      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `<!DOCTYPE` or `<html`, the server serves it as-is (just injects the helper [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m script). Otherwise, the server automatically wraps your content in the      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m frame template — adding the header, CSS theme, selection indicator, and all [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m interactive infrastructure. **Write content fragments by default.** Only    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m write full documents when you need complete control over the page.          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Starting a Session                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Start server with persistence (mockups saved to project)                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts/start-server.sh --project-dir /path/to/project                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Returns:                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m {"type":"server-started","port":52341,"url":"http://localhost:52341",       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "screen_dir":"/path/to/project/.superpowers/brainstorm/12345-1706000000/con [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m tent",                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "state_dir":"/path/to/project/.superpowers/brainstorm/12345-1706000000/stat [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m e"}                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Save `screen_dir` and `state_dir` from the response. Tell user to open the  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m URL.                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Finding connection info:** The server writes its startup JSON to          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `$STATE_DIR/server-info`. If you launched the server in the background and  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m didn't capture stdout, read that file to get the URL and port. When using   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `--project-dir`, check `<project>/.superpowers/brainstorm/` for the session [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m directory.                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Note:** Pass the project root as `--project-dir` so mockups persist in    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `.superpowers/brainstorm/` and survive server restarts. Without it, files   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m go to `/tmp` and get cleaned up. Remind the user to add `.superpowers/` to  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `.gitignore` if it's not already there.                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Launching the server by platform:**                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Claude Code (macOS / Linux):**                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Default mode works — the script backgrounds the server itself             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts/start-server.sh --project-dir /path/to/project                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Claude Code (Windows):**                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Windows auto-detects and uses foreground mode, which blocks the tool      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m call.                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Use run_in_background: true on the powershell tool call so the server     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m survives                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # across conversation turns.                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts/start-server.sh --project-dir /path/to/project                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When calling this via the powershell tool, set `run_in_background: true`.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Then read `$STATE_DIR/server-info` on the next turn to get the URL and      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m port.                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Codex:**                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Codex reaps background processes. The script auto-detects CODEX_CI and    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # switches to foreground mode. Run it normally — no extra flags needed.     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts/start-server.sh --project-dir /path/to/project                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Gemini CLI:**                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Use --foreground and set is_background: true on your shell tool call      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # so the process survives across turns                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts/start-server.sh --project-dir /path/to/project --foreground         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Other environments:** The server must keep running in the background      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m across conversation turns. If your environment reaps detached processes,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m use `--foreground` and launch the command with your platform's background   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m execution mechanism.                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If the URL is unreachable from your browser (common in remote/containerized [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m setups), bind a non-loopback host:                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts/start-server.sh \                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   --project-dir /path/to/project \                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   --host 0.0.0.0 \                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   --url-host localhost                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use `--url-host` to control what hostname is printed in the returned URL    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m JSON.                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## The Loop                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Check server is alive**, then **write HTML** to a new file in          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `screen_dir`:                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Before each write, check that `$STATE_DIR/server-info` exists. If it   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m doesn't (or `$STATE_DIR/server-stopped` exists), the server has shut down — [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m restart it with `start-server.sh` before continuing. The server auto-exits  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m after 30 minutes of inactivity.                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Use semantic filenames: `platform.html`, `visual-style.html`,          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `layout.html`                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - **Never reuse filenames** — each screen gets a fresh file              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Use Write tool — **never use cat/heredoc** (dumps noise into           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m execute_powershell)                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Server automatically serves the newest file                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Tell user what to expect and end your turn:**                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Remind them of the URL (every step, not just first)                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Give a brief text summary of what's on screen (e.g., "Showing 3 layout [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m options for the homepage")                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Ask them to respond in the execute_powershell: "Take a look and let me [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m know what you think. Click to select an option if you'd like."              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **On your next turn** — after the user responds in the                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m execute_powershell:                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Read `$STATE_DIR/events` if it exists — this contains the user's       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m browser interactions (clicks, selections) as JSON lines                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Merge with the user's execute_powershell text to get the full picture  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - The execute_powershell message is the primary feedback;                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `state_dir/events` provides structured interaction data                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Iterate or advance** — if feedback changes current screen, write a new [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m file (e.g., `layout-v2.html`). Only move to the next question when the      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m current step is validated.                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. **Unload when returning to execute_powershell** — when the next step     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m doesn't need the browser (e.g., a clarifying question, a tradeoff           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m discussion), push a waiting screen to clear the stale content:              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```html                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    <!-- filename: waiting.html (or waiting-2.html, etc.) -->                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    <div                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;min-height:60 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m vh">                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m      <p class="subtitle">Continuing in execute_powershell...</p>            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    </div>                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    This prevents the user from staring at a resolved choice while the       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m conversation has moved on. When the next visual question comes up, push a   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m new content file as usual.                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 6. Repeat until done.                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Writing Content Fragments                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Write just the content that goes inside the page. The server wraps it in    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the frame template automatically (header, theme CSS, selection indicator,   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and all interactive infrastructure).                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Minimal example:**                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <h2>Which layout works better?</h2>                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <p class="subtitle">Consider readability and visual hierarchy</p>           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="options">                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="option" data-choice="a" onclick="toggleSelect(this)">         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="letter">A</div>                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="content">                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <h3>Single Column</h3>                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <p>Clean, focused reading experience</p>                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     </div>                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   </div>                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="option" data-choice="b" onclick="toggleSelect(this)">         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="letter">B</div>                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="content">                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <h3>Two Column</h3>                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <p>Sidebar navigation with main content</p>                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     </div>                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   </div>                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m That's it. No `<html>`, no CSS, no `<script>` tags needed. The server       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m provides all of that.                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## CSS Classes Available                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The frame template provides these CSS classes for your content:             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Options (A/B/C choices)                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="options">                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="option" data-choice="a" onclick="toggleSelect(this)">         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="letter">A</div>                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="content">                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <h3>Title</h3>                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <p>Description</p>                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     </div>                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   </div>                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Multi-select:** Add `data-multiselect` to the container to let users      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m select multiple options. Each click toggles the item. The indicator bar     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m shows the count.                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="options" data-multiselect>                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <!-- same option markup — users can select/deselect multiple -->          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Cards (visual designs)                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="cards">                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="card" data-choice="design1" onclick="toggleSelect(this)">     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="card-image"><!-- mockup content --></div>                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     <div class="card-body">                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <h3>Name</h3>                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       <p>Description</p>                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     </div>                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   </div>                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Mockup container                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="mockup">                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="mockup-header">Preview: Dashboard Layout</div>                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="mockup-body"><!-- your mockup HTML --></div>                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Split view (side-by-side)                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="split">                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="mockup"><!-- left --></div>                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="mockup"><!-- right --></div>                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Pros/Cons                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="pros-cons">                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="pros"><h4>Pros</h4><ul><li>Benefit</li></ul></div>            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="cons"><h4>Cons</h4><ul><li>Drawback</li></ul></div>           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Mock elements (wireframe building blocks)                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```html                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="mock-nav">Logo | Home | About | Contact</div>                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div style="display: flex;">                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="mock-sidebar">Navigation</div>                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   <div class="mock-content">Main content area</div>                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </div>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <button class="mock-button">Action Button</button>                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <input class="mock-input" placeholder="Input field">                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <div class="placeholder">Placeholder area</div>                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Typography and sections                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `h2` — page title                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `h3` — section heading                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `.subtitle` — secondary text below title                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `.section` — content block with bottom margin                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `.label` — small uppercase label text                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Browser Events Format                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When the user clicks options in the browser, their interactions are         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m recorded to `$STATE_DIR/events` (one JSON object per line). The file is     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m cleared automatically when you push a new screen.                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```jsonl                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m {"type":"click","choice":"a","text":"Option A - Simple                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Layout","timestamp":1706000101}                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m {"type":"click","choice":"c","text":"Option C - Complex                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Grid","timestamp":1706000108}                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m {"type":"click","choice":"b","text":"Option B -                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Hybrid","timestamp":1706000115}                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The full event stream shows the user's exploration path — they may click    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m multiple options before settling. The last `choice` event is typically the  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m final selection, but the pattern of clicks can reveal hesitation or         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m preferences worth asking about.                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If `$STATE_DIR/events` doesn't exist, the user didn't interact with the     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m browser — use only their execute_powershell text.                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Design Tips                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Scale fidelity to the question** — wireframes for layout, polish for    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m polish questions                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Explain the question on each page** — "Which layout feels more          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m professional?" not just "Pick one"                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Iterate before advancing** — if feedback changes current screen, write  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m a new version                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **2-4 options max** per screen                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Use real content when it matters** — for a photography portfolio, use   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m actual images (Unsplash). Placeholder content obscures design issues.       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Keep mockups simple** — focus on layout and structure, not              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m pixel-perfect design                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## File Naming                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Use semantic names: `platform.html`, `visual-style.html`, `layout.html`   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Never reuse filenames — each screen must be a new file                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - For iterations: append version suffix like `layout-v2.html`,              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `layout-v3.html`                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Server serves newest file by modification time                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Cleaning Up                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts/stop-server.sh $SESSION_DIR                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If the session used `--project-dir`, mockup files persist in                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `.superpowers/brainstorm/` for later reference. Only `/tmp` sessions get    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m deleted on stop.                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Reference                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Frame template (CSS reference): `scripts/frame-template.html`             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Helper script (client-side): `scripts/helper.js`                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
