[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## Code Organization                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     You reason best about code you can hold in context at once, and your    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m edits are more                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     reliable when files are focused. Keep this in mind:                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Follow the file structure defined in the plan                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Each file should have one clear responsibility with a well-defined    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m interface                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - If a file you're creating is growing beyond the plan's intent, stop   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and report                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       it as DONE_WITH_CONCERNS — don't split files on your own without plan [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m guidance                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - If an existing file you're modifying is already large or tangled,     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m work carefully                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       and note it as a concern in your report                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - In existing codebases, follow established patterns. Improve code      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m you're touching                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       the way a good developer would, but don't restructure things outside  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m your task.                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## When You're in Over Your Head                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     It is always OK to stop and say "this is too hard for me." Bad work is  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m worse than                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     no work. You will not be penalized for escalating.                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **STOP and escalate when:**                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - The task requires architectural decisions with multiple valid         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m approaches                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - You need to understand code beyond what was provided and can't find   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m clarity                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - You feel uncertain about whether your approach is correct             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - The task involves restructuring existing code in ways the plan didn't [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m anticipate                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - You've been reading file after file trying to understand the system   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m without progress                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **How to escalate:** Report back with status BLOCKED or NEEDS_CONTEXT.  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Describe                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     specifically what you're stuck on, what you've tried, and what kind of  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m help you need.                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     The controller can provide more context, re-dispatch with a more        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m capable model,                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     or break the task into smaller pieces.                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## Before Reporting Back: Self-Review                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     Review your work with fresh eyes. Ask yourself:                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Completeness:**                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Did I fully implement everything in the spec?                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Did I miss any requirements?                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Are there edge cases I didn't handle?                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Quality:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Is this my best work?                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Are names clear and accurate (match what things do, not how they      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m work)?                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Is the code clean and maintainable?                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Discipline:**                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Did I avoid overbuilding (YAGNI)?                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Did I only build what was requested?                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Did I follow existing patterns in the codebase?                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     **Testing:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Do tests actually verify behavior (not just mock behavior)?           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Did I follow TDD if required?                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Are tests comprehensive?                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     If you find issues during self-review, fix them now before reporting.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ## Report Format                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     When done, report:                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - **Status:** DONE | DONE_WITH_CONCERNS | BLOCKED | NEEDS_CONTEXT       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - What you implemented (or what you attempted, if blocked)              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - What you tested and test results                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Files changed                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Self-review findings (if any)                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     - Any issues or concerns                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     Use DONE_WITH_CONCERNS if you completed the work but have doubts about  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m correctness.                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     Use BLOCKED if you cannot complete the task. Use NEEDS_CONTEXT if you   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m need                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     information that wasn't provided. Never silently produce work you're    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m unsure about.                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
