[36m│[0m [superpowers/systematic-debugging/condition-based-waiting]]                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Condition-Based Waiting                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Overview                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Flaky tests often guess at timing with arbitrary delays. This creates race  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m conditions where tests pass on fast machines but fail under load or in CI.  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Core principle:** Wait for the actual condition you care about, not a     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m guess about how long it takes.                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## When to Use                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```dot                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m digraph when_to_use {                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Test uses setTimeout/sleep?" [shape=diamond];                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Testing timing behavior?" [shape=diamond];                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Document WHY timeout needed" [shape=box];                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Use condition-based waiting" [shape=box];                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Test uses setTimeout/sleep?" -> "Testing timing behavior?"             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [label="yes"];                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Testing timing behavior?" -> "Document WHY timeout needed"             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [label="yes"];                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Testing timing behavior?" -> "Use condition-based waiting"             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [label="no"];                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Use when:**                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Tests have arbitrary delays (`setTimeout`, `sleep`, `time.sleep()`)       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Tests are flaky (pass sometimes, fail under load)                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Tests timeout when run in parallel                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Waiting for async operations to complete                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Don't use when:**                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Testing actual timing behavior (debounce, throttle intervals)             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Always document WHY if using arbitrary timeout                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Core Pattern                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m // ❌ BEFORE: Guessing at timing                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 50));                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m const result = getResult();                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m expect(result).toBeDefined();                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m // ✅ AFTER: Waiting for condition                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m await waitFor(() => getResult() !== undefined);                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m const result = getResult();                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m expect(result).toBeDefined();                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Quick Patterns                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Scenario | Pattern |                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |----------|---------|                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Wait for event | `waitFor(() => events.find(e => e.type === 'DONE'))` |   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Wait for state | `waitFor(() => machine.state === 'ready')` |             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Wait for count | `waitFor(() => items.length >= 5)` |                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Wait for file | `waitFor(() => fs.existsSync(path))` |                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Complex condition | `waitFor(() => obj.ready && obj.value > 10)` |        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Implementation                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Generic polling function:                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m async function waitFor<T>(                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   condition: () => T | undefined | null | false,                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   description: string,                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   timeoutMs = 5000                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ): Promise<T> {                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   const startTime = Date.now();                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   while (true) {                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     const result = condition();                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     if (result) return result;                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     if (Date.now() - startTime > timeoutMs) {                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       throw new Error(`Timeout waiting for ${description} after             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ${timeoutMs}ms`);                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     }                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 10)); // Poll every 10ms           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   }                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m See `condition-based-waiting-example.ts` in this directory for complete     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m implementation with domain-specific helpers (`waitForEvent`,                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `waitForEventCount`, `waitForEventMatch`) from actual debugging session.    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Common Mistakes                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Polling too fast:** `setTimeout(check, 1)` - wastes CPU                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **✅ Fix:** Poll every 10ms                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ No timeout:** Loop forever if condition never met                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **✅ Fix:** Always include timeout with clear error                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Stale data:** Cache state before loop                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **✅ Fix:** Call getter inside loop for fresh data                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## When Arbitrary Timeout IS Correct                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m // Tool ticks every 100ms - need 2 ticks to verify partial output           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m await waitForEvent(manager, 'TOOL_STARTED'); // First: wait for condition   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 200));   // Then: wait for timed       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m behavior                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m // 200ms = 2 ticks at 100ms intervals - documented and justified            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Requirements:**                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. First wait for triggering condition                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Based on known timing (not guessing)                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Comment explaining WHY                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Real-World Impact                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m From debugging session (2025-10-03):                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Fixed 15 flaky tests across 3 files                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Pass rate: 60% → 100%                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Execution time: 40% faster                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - No more race conditions                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
