[36m│[0m ## Source Material                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Extracted debugging framework from `/Users/jesse/.claude/CLAUDE.md`:        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - 4-phase systematic process (Investigation → Pattern Analysis → Hypothesis [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m → Implementation)                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Core mandate: ALWAYS find root cause, NEVER fix symptoms                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Rules designed to resist time pressure and rationalization                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Extraction Decisions                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What to include:**                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Complete 4-phase framework with all rules                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Anti-shortcuts ("NEVER fix symptom", "STOP and re-analyze")               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Pressure-resistant language ("even if faster", "even if I seem in a       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m hurry")                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Concrete steps for each phase                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What to leave out:**                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Project-specific context                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Repetitive variations of same rule                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Narrative explanations (condensed to principles)                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Structure Following skill-creation/SKILL.md                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Rich when_to_use** - Included symptoms and anti-patterns               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Type: technique** - Concrete process with steps                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Keywords** - "root cause", "symptom", "workaround", "debugging",       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "investigation"                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Flowchart** - Decision point for "fix failed" → re-analyze vs add more [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fixes                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. **Phase-by-phase breakdown** - Scannable checklist format                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 6. **Anti-patterns section** - What NOT to do (critical for this skill)     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Bulletproofing Elements                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Framework designed to resist rationalization under pressure:                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Language Choices                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "ALWAYS" / "NEVER" (not "should" / "try to")                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "even if faster" / "even if I seem in a hurry"                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "STOP and re-analyze" (explicit pause)                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Don't skip past" (catches the actual behavior)                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Structural Defenses                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Phase 1 required** - Can't skip to implementation                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Single hypothesis rule** - Forces thinking, prevents shotgun fixes      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Explicit failure mode** - "IF your first fix doesn't work" with         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m mandatory action                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **Anti-patterns section** - Shows exactly what shortcuts look like        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Redundancy                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Root cause mandate in overview + when_to_use + Phase 1 + implementation   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m rules                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "NEVER fix symptom" appears 4 times in different contexts                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Each phase has explicit "don't skip" guidance                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Testing Approach                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Created 4 validation tests following                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m skills/meta/testing-skills-with-subagents:                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
