[36m│[0m [BEGIN context from [superpowers/systematic-debugging/defense-in-depth]]    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Defense-in-Depth Validation                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Overview                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When you fix a bug caused by invalid data, adding validation at one place   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m feels sufficient. But that single check can be bypassed by different code   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m paths, refactoring, or mocks.                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Core principle:** Validate at EVERY layer data passes through. Make the   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m bug structurally impossible.                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Why Multiple Layers                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Single validation: "We fixed the bug"                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Multiple layers: "We made the bug impossible"                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Different layers catch different cases:                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Entry validation catches most bugs                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Business logic catches edge cases                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Environment guards prevent context-specific dangers                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Debug logging helps when other layers fail                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## The Four Layers                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Layer 1: Entry Point Validation                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Purpose:** Reject obviously invalid input at API boundary                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m function createProject(name: string, workingDirectory: string) {            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   if (!workingDirectory || workingDirectory.trim() === '') {                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     throw new Error('workingDirectory cannot be empty');                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   }                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   if (!existsSync(workingDirectory)) {                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     throw new Error(`workingDirectory does not exist:                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ${workingDirectory}`);                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   }                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   if (!statSync(workingDirectory).isDirectory()) {                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     throw new Error(`workingDirectory is not a directory:                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ${workingDirectory}`);                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   }                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   // ... proceed                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Layer 2: Business Logic Validation                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Purpose:** Ensure data makes sense for this operation                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m function initializeWorkspace(projectDir: string, sessionId: string) {       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   if (!projectDir) {                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     throw new Error('projectDir required for workspace initialization');    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   }                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   // ... proceed                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Layer 3: Environment Guards                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Purpose:** Prevent dangerous operations in specific contexts              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m async function gitInit(directory: string) {                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   // In tests, refuse git init outside temp directories                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'test') {                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     const normalized = normalize(resolve(directory));                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     const tmpDir = normalize(resolve(tmpdir()));                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     if (!normalized.startsWith(tmpDir)) {                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       throw new Error(                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         `Refusing git init outside temp dir during tests: ${directory}`     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m       );                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     }                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   }                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   // ... proceed                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Layer 4: Debug Instrumentation                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Purpose:** Capture context for forensics                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m async function gitInit(directory: string) {                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   const stack = new Error().stack;                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   logger.debug('About to git init', {                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     directory,                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     cwd: process.cwd(),                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     stack,                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   });                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   // ... proceed                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Applying the Pattern                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When you find a bug:                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Trace the data flow** - Where does bad value originate? Where used?    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Map all checkpoints** - List every point data passes through           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Add validation at each layer** - Entry, business, environment, debug   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Test each layer** - Try to bypass layer 1, verify layer 2 catches it   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Example from Session                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Bug: Empty `projectDir` caused `git init` in source code                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Data flow:**                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Test setup → empty string                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. `Project.create(name, '')`                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. `WorkspaceManager.createWorkspace('')`                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. `git init` runs in `process.cwd()`                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Four layers added:**                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 1: `Project.create()` validates not empty/exists/writable           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 2: `WorkspaceManager` validates projectDir not empty                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 3: `WorktreeManager` refuses git init outside tmpdir in tests       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 4: Stack trace logging before git init                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Result:** All 1847 tests passed, bug impossible to reproduce              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Key Insight                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m All four layers were necessary. During testing, each layer caught bugs the  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m others missed:                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Different code paths bypassed entry validation                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Mocks bypassed business logic checks                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Edge cases on different platforms needed environment guards               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Debug logging identified structural misuse                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Don't stop at one validation point.** Add checks at every layer.          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [BEGIN context from [superpowers/systematic-debugging/root-cause-tracing]]  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Root Cause Tracing                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Overview                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Bugs often manifest deep in the call stack (git init in wrong directory,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m file created in wrong location, database opened with wrong path). Your      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m instinct is to fix where the error appears, but that's treating a symptom.  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Core principle:** Trace backward through the call chain until you find    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the original trigger, then fix at the source.                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## When to Use                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```dot                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m digraph when_to_use {                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Bug appears deep in stack?" [shape=diamond];                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Can trace backwards?" [shape=diamond];                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Fix at symptom point" [shape=box];                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Trace to original trigger" [shape=box];                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "BETTER: Also add defense-in-depth" [shape=box];                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Bug appears deep in stack?" -> "Can trace backwards?" [label="yes"];   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Can trace backwards?" -> "Trace to original trigger" [label="yes"];    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Can trace backwards?" -> "Fix at symptom point" [label="no - dead      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m end"];                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Trace to original trigger" -> "BETTER: Also add defense-in-depth";     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Use when:**                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Error happens deep in execution (not at entry point)                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Stack trace shows long call chain                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Unclear where invalid data originated                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Need to find which test/code triggers the problem                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## The Tracing Process                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 1. Observe the Symptom                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Error: git init failed in /Users/jesse/project/packages/core                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 2. Find Immediate Cause                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What code directly causes this?**                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m await execFileAsync('git', ['init'], { cwd: projectDir });                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 3. Ask: What Called This?                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m WorktreeManager.createSessionWorktree(projectDir, sessionId)                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   → called by Session.initializeWorkspace()                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   → called by Session.create()                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   → called by test at Project.create()                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 4. Keep Tracing Up                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What value was passed?**                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `projectDir = ''` (empty string!)                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Empty string as `cwd` resolves to `process.cwd()`                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - That's the source code directory!                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 5. Find Original Trigger                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Where did empty string come from?**                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m const context = setupCoreTest(); // Returns { tempDir: '' }                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Project.create('name', context.tempDir); // Accessed before beforeEach!     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Adding Stack Traces                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When you can't trace manually, add instrumentation:                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```typescript                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m // Before the problematic operation                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m async function gitInit(directory: string) {                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   const stack = new Error().stack;                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   console.error('DEBUG git init:', {                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     directory,                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     cwd: process.cwd(),                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     nodeEnv: process.env.NODE_ENV,                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     stack,                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   });                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   await execFileAsync('git', ['init'], { cwd: directory });                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Critical:** Use `console.error()` in tests (not logger - may not show)    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Run and capture:**                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m npm test 2>&1 | grep 'DEBUG git init'                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Analyze stack traces:**                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Look for test file names                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Find the line number triggering the call                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Identify the pattern (same test? same parameter?)                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Finding Which Test Causes Pollution                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If something appears during tests but you don't know which test:            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use the bisection script `find-polluter.sh` in this directory:              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ./find-polluter.sh '.git' 'src/**/*.test.ts'                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Runs tests one-by-one, stops at first polluter. See script for usage.       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Real Example: Empty projectDir                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Symptom:** `.git` created in `packages/core/` (source code)               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Trace chain:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. `git init` runs in `process.cwd()` ← empty cwd parameter                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. WorktreeManager called with empty projectDir                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Session.create() passed empty string                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. Test accessed `context.tempDir` before beforeEach                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. setupCoreTest() returns `{ tempDir: '' }` initially                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Root cause:** Top-level variable initialization accessing empty value     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Fix:** Made tempDir a getter that throws if accessed before beforeEach    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Also added defense-in-depth:**                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 1: Project.create() validates directory                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 2: WorkspaceManager validates not empty                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 3: NODE_ENV guard refuses git init outside tmpdir                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Layer 4: Stack trace logging before git init                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Key Principle                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```dot                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m digraph principle {                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Found immediate cause" [shape=ellipse];                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Can trace one level up?" [shape=diamond];                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Trace backwards" [shape=box];                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Is this the source?" [shape=diamond];                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Fix at source" [shape=box];                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Add validation at each layer" [shape=box];                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Bug impossible" [shape=doublecircle];                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "NEVER fix just the symptom" [shape=octagon, style=filled,              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fillcolor=red, fontcolor=white];                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Found immediate cause" -> "Can trace one level up?";                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Can trace one level up?" -> "Trace backwards" [label="yes"];           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Can trace one level up?" -> "NEVER fix just the symptom" [label="no"]; [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Trace backwards" -> "Is this the source?";                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Is this the source?" -> "Trace backwards" [label="no - keeps going"];  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Is this the source?" -> "Fix at source" [label="yes"];                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Fix at source" -> "Add validation at each layer";                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Add validation at each layer" -> "Bug impossible";                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **NEVER fix just where the error appears.** Trace back to find the original [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m trigger.                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Stack Trace Tips                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **In tests:** Use `console.error()` not logger - logger may be suppressed   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Before operation:** Log before the dangerous operation, not after it      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fails                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Include context:** Directory, cwd, environment variables, timestamps      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Capture stack:** `new Error().stack` shows complete call chain            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
