[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The complete Skill directory structure might look like this:                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m pdf/                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ├── SKILL.md              # Main instructions (loaded when triggered)       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ├── FORMS.md              # Form-filling guide (loaded as needed)           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ├── reference.md          # API reference (loaded as needed)                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ├── examples.md           # Usage examples (loaded as needed)               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m └── scripts/                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ├── analyze_form.py   # Utility script (executed, not loaded)           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ├── fill_form.py      # Form filling script                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     └── validate.py       # Validation script                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #### Pattern 1: High-level guide with references                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ---                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m name: PDF Processing                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m description: Extracts text and tables from PDF files, fills forms, and      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m merges documents. Use when working with PDF files or when the user mentions [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m PDFs, forms, or document extraction.                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ---                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # PDF Processing                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Quick start                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Extract text with pdfplumber:                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m import pdfplumber                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m with pdfplumber.open("file.pdf") as pdf:                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     text = pdf.pages[0].extract_text()                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Advanced features                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Form filling**: See [FORMS.md](FORMS.md) for complete guide               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **API reference**: See [REFERENCE.md](REFERENCE.md) for all methods         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Examples**: See [EXAMPLES.md](EXAMPLES.md) for common patterns            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude loads FORMS.md, REFERENCE.md, or EXAMPLES.md only when needed.       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #### Pattern 2: Domain-specific organization                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For Skills with multiple domains, organize content by domain to avoid       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m loading irrelevant context. When a user asks about sales metrics, Claude    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m only needs to read sales-related schemas, not finance or marketing data.    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This keeps token usage low and context focused.                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m bigquery-skill/                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ├── SKILL.md (overview and navigation)                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m └── reference/                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ├── finance.md (revenue, billing metrics)                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ├── sales.md (opportunities, pipeline)                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ├── product.md (API usage, features)                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     └── marketing.md (campaigns, attribution)                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown SKILL.md theme={null}                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # BigQuery Data Analysis                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Available datasets                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Finance**: Revenue, ARR, billing → See                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [reference/finance.md](reference/finance.md)                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Sales**: Opportunities, pipeline, accounts → See                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [reference/sales.md](reference/sales.md)                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Product**: API usage, features, adoption → See                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [reference/product.md](reference/product.md)                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Marketing**: Campaigns, attribution, email → See                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [reference/marketing.md](reference/marketing.md)                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Quick search                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Find specific metrics using grep:                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m grep -i "revenue" reference/finance.md                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m grep -i "pipeline" reference/sales.md                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m grep -i "api usage" reference/product.md                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m #### Pattern 3: Conditional details                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Show basic content, link to advanced content:                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # DOCX Processing                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Creating documents                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use docx-js for new documents. See [DOCX-JS.md](DOCX-JS.md).                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Editing documents                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For simple edits, modify the XML directly.                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **For tracked changes**: See [REDLINING.md](REDLINING.md)                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **For OOXML details**: See [OOXML.md](OOXML.md)                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude reads REDLINING.md or OOXML.md only when the user needs those        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m features.                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Avoid deeply nested references                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude may partially read files when they're referenced from other          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m referenced files. When encountering nested references, Claude might use     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m commands like `head -100` to preview content rather than reading entire     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m files, resulting in incomplete information.                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Keep references one level deep from SKILL.md**. All reference files       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m should link directly from SKILL.md to ensure Claude reads complete files    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m when needed.                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad example: Too deep**:                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # SKILL.md                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m See [advanced.md](advanced.md)...                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # advanced.md                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m See [details.md](details.md)...                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # details.md                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Here's the actual information...                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good example: One level deep**:                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # SKILL.md                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Basic usage**: [instructions in SKILL.md]                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Advanced features**: See [advanced.md](advanced.md)                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **API reference**: See [reference.md](reference.md)                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Examples**: See [examples.md](examples.md)                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Structure longer reference files with table of contents                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For reference files longer than 100 lines, include a table of contents at   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the top. This ensures Claude can see the full scope of available            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m information even when previewing with partial reads.                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example**:                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # API Reference                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Contents                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Authentication and setup                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Core methods (create, read, update, delete)                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Advanced features (batch operations, webhooks)                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Error handling patterns                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Code examples                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Authentication and setup                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ...                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Core methods                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ...                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude can then read the complete file or jump to specific sections as      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m needed.                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For details on how this filesystem-based architecture enables progressive   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m disclosure, see the [Runtime environment](#runtime-environment) section in  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the Advanced section below.                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Workflows and feedback loops                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Use workflows for complex tasks                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Break complex operations into clear, sequential steps. For particularly     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m complex workflows, provide a checklist that Claude can copy into its        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m response and check off as it progresses.                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example 1: Research synthesis workflow** (for Skills without code):       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Research synthesis workflow                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Copy this checklist and track your progress:                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Research Progress:                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 1: Read all source documents                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 2: Identify key themes                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 3: Cross-reference claims                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 4: Create structured summary                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 5: Verify citations                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 1: Read all source documents**                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Review each document in the `sources/` directory. Note the main arguments   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and supporting evidence.                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 2: Identify key themes**                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Look for patterns across sources. What themes appear repeatedly? Where do   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m sources agree or disagree?                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 3: Cross-reference claims**                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For each major claim, verify it appears in the source material. Note which  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m source supports each point.                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 4: Create structured summary**                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Organize findings by theme. Include:                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Main claim                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Supporting evidence from sources                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Conflicting viewpoints (if any)                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 5: Verify citations**                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Check that every claim references the correct source document. If citations [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m are incomplete, return to Step 3.                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This example shows how workflows apply to analysis tasks that don't require [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m code. The checklist pattern works for any complex, multi-step process.      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example 2: PDF form filling workflow** (for Skills with code):            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## PDF form filling workflow                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Copy this checklist and check off items as you complete them:               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Task Progress:                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 1: Analyze the form (run analyze_form.py)                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 2: Create field mapping (edit fields.json)                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 3: Validate mapping (run validate_fields.py)                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 4: Fill the form (run fill_form.py)                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Step 5: Verify output (run verify_output.py)                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 1: Analyze the form**                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Run: `python scripts/analyze_form.py input.pdf`                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This extracts form fields and their locations, saving to `fields.json`.     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 2: Create field mapping**                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Edit `fields.json` to add values for each field.                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 3: Validate mapping**                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Run: `python scripts/validate_fields.py fields.json`                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Fix any validation errors before continuing.                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 4: Fill the form**                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Run: `python scripts/fill_form.py input.pdf fields.json output.pdf`         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Step 5: Verify output**                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Run: `python scripts/verify_output.py output.pdf`                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If verification fails, return to Step 2.                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Clear steps prevent Claude from skipping critical validation. The checklist [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m helps both Claude and you track progress through multi-step workflows.      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Implement feedback loops                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Common pattern**: Run validator → fix errors → repeat                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This pattern greatly improves output quality.                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example 1: Style guide compliance** (for Skills without code):            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Content review process                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Draft your content following the guidelines in STYLE_GUIDE.md            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Review against the checklist:                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Check terminology consistency                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Verify examples follow the standard format                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Confirm all required sections are present                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. If issues found:                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Note each issue with specific section reference                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Revise the content                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Review the checklist again                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. Only proceed when all requirements are met                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. Finalize and save the document                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This shows the validation loop pattern using reference documents instead of [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scripts. The "validator" is STYLE\_GUIDE.md, and Claude performs the check  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m by reading and comparing.                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example 2: Document editing process** (for Skills with code):             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Document editing process                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Make your edits to `word/document.xml`                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Validate immediately**: `python ooxml/scripts/validate.py              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m unpacked_dir/`                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. If validation fails:                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Review the error message carefully                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Fix the issues in the XML                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Run validation again                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Only proceed when validation passes**                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. Rebuild: `python ooxml/scripts/pack.py unpacked_dir/ output.docx`        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 6. Test the output document                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The validation loop catches errors early.                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Content guidelines                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Avoid time-sensitive information                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Don't include information that will become outdated:                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad example: Time-sensitive** (will become wrong):                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If you're doing this before August 2025, use the old API.                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m After August 2025, use the new API.                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good example** (use "old patterns" section):                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Current method                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use the v2 API endpoint: `api.example.com/v2/messages`                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Old patterns                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <details>                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <summary>Legacy v1 API (deprecated 2025-08)</summary>                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The v1 API used: `api.example.com/v1/messages`                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This endpoint is no longer supported.                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </details>                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The old patterns section provides historical context without cluttering the [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m main content.                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Use consistent terminology                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Choose one term and use it throughout the Skill:                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good - Consistent**:                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Always "API endpoint"                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Always "field"                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Always "extract"                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad - Inconsistent**:                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Mix "API endpoint", "URL", "API route", "path"                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Mix "field", "box", "element", "control"                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Mix "extract", "pull", "get", "retrieve"                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Consistency helps Claude understand and follow instructions.                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Common patterns                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Template pattern                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Provide templates for output format. Match the level of strictness to your  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m needs.                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **For strict requirements** (like API responses or data formats):           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Report structure                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ALWAYS use this exact template structure:                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # [Analysis Title]                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Executive summary                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [One-paragraph overview of key findings]                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Key findings                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Finding 1 with supporting data                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Finding 2 with supporting data                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Finding 3 with supporting data                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Recommendations                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Specific actionable recommendation                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Specific actionable recommendation                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **For flexible guidance** (when adaptation is useful):                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Report structure                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Here is a sensible default format, but use your best judgment based on the  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m analysis:                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # [Analysis Title]                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Executive summary                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [Overview]                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Key findings                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [Adapt sections based on what you discover]                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Recommendations                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [Tailor to the specific context]                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Adjust sections as needed for the specific analysis type.                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Examples pattern                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For Skills where output quality depends on seeing examples, provide         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m input/output pairs just like in regular prompting:                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Commit message format                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Generate commit messages following these examples:                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example 1:**                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Input: Added user authentication with JWT tokens                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Output:                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m feat(auth): implement JWT-based authentication                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Add login endpoint and token validation middleware                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example 2:**                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Input: Fixed bug where dates displayed incorrectly in reports               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Output:                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fix(reports): correct date formatting in timezone conversion                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use UTC timestamps consistently across report generation                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example 3:**                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Input: Updated dependencies and refactored error handling                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Output:                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m chore: update dependencies and refactor error handling                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Upgrade lodash to 4.17.21                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Standardize error response format across endpoints                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Follow this style: type(scope): brief description, then detailed            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m explanation.                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Examples help Claude understand the desired style and level of detail more  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m clearly than descriptions alone.                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Conditional workflow pattern                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Guide Claude through decision points:                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Document modification workflow                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Determine the modification type:                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    **Creating new content?** → Follow "Creation workflow" below             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    **Editing existing content?** → Follow "Editing workflow" below          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Creation workflow:                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Use docx-js library                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Build document from scratch                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Export to .docx format                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Editing workflow:                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Unpack existing document                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Modify XML directly                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Validate after each change                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Repack when complete                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <Tip>                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   If workflows become large or complicated with many steps, consider        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m pushing them into separate files and tell Claude to read the appropriate    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m file based on the task at hand.                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </Tip>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Evaluation and iteration                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Build evaluations first                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Create evaluations BEFORE writing extensive documentation.** This ensures [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m your Skill solves real problems rather than documenting imagined ones.      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Evaluation-driven development:**                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Identify gaps**: Run Claude on representative tasks without a Skill.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Document specific failures or missing context                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Create evaluations**: Build three scenarios that test these gaps       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Establish baseline**: Measure Claude's performance without the Skill   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Write minimal instructions**: Create just enough content to address    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the gaps and pass evaluations                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. **Iterate**: Execute evaluations, compare against baseline, and refine   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This approach ensures you're solving actual problems rather than            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m anticipating requirements that may never materialize.                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Evaluation structure**:                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```json  theme={null}                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m {                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   "skills": ["pdf-processing"],                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   "query": "Extract all text from this PDF file and save it to output.txt", [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   "files": ["test-files/document.pdf"],                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   "expected_behavior": [                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Successfully reads the PDF file using an appropriate PDF processing    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m library or command-line tool",                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Extracts text content from all pages in the document without missing   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m any pages",                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     "Saves the extracted text to a file named output.txt in a clear,        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m readable format"                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   ]                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <Note>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   This example demonstrates a data-driven evaluation with a simple testing  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m rubric. We do not currently provide a built-in way to run these             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m evaluations. Users can create their own evaluation system. Evaluations are  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m your source of truth for measuring Skill effectiveness.                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </Note>                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Develop Skills iteratively with Claude                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The most effective Skill development process involves Claude itself. Work   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m with one instance of Claude ("Claude A") to create a Skill that will be     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m used by other instances ("Claude B"). Claude A helps you design and refine  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m instructions, while Claude B tests them in real tasks. This works because   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude models understand both how to write effective agent instructions and [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m what information agents need.                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Creating a new Skill:**                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Complete a task without a Skill**: Work through a problem with Claude  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m A using normal prompting. As you work, you'll naturally provide context,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m explain preferences, and share procedural knowledge. Notice what            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m information you repeatedly provide.                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Identify the reusable pattern**: After completing the task, identify   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m what context you provided that would be useful for similar future tasks.    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    **Example**: If you worked through a BigQuery analysis, you might have   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m provided table names, field definitions, filtering rules (like "always      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m exclude test accounts"), and common query patterns.                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Ask Claude A to create a Skill**: "Create a Skill that captures this   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m BigQuery analysis pattern we just used. Include the table schemas, naming   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m conventions, and the rule about filtering test accounts."                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    <Tip>                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m      Claude models understand the Skill format and structure natively. You  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m don't need special system prompts or a "writing skills" skill to get Claude [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m to help create Skills. Simply ask Claude to create a Skill and it will      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m generate properly structured SKILL.md content with appropriate frontmatter  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and body content.                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    </Tip>                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Review for conciseness**: Check that Claude A hasn't added unnecessary [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m explanations. Ask: "Remove the explanation about what win rate means -      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude already knows that."                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. **Improve information architecture**: Ask Claude A to organize the       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m content more effectively. For example: "Organize this so the table schema   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m is in a separate reference file. We might add more tables later."           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 6. **Test on similar tasks**: Use the Skill with Claude B (a fresh instance [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m with the Skill loaded) on related use cases. Observe whether Claude B finds [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the right information, applies rules correctly, and handles the task        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m successfully.                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 7. **Iterate based on observation**: If Claude B struggles or misses        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m something, return to Claude A with specifics: "When Claude used this Skill, [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m it forgot to filter by date for Q4. Should we add a section about date      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m filtering patterns?"                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Iterating on existing Skills:**                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The same hierarchical pattern continues when improving Skills. You          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m alternate between:                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Working with Claude A** (the expert who helps refine the Skill)         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Testing with Claude B** (the agent using the Skill to perform real      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m work)                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Observing Claude B's behavior** and bringing insights back to Claude A  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Use the Skill in real workflows**: Give Claude B (with the Skill       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m loaded) actual tasks, not test scenarios                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Observe Claude B's behavior**: Note where it struggles, succeeds, or   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m makes unexpected choices                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    **Example observation**: "When I asked Claude B for a regional sales     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m report, it wrote the query but forgot to filter out test accounts, even     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m though the Skill mentions this rule."                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Return to Claude A for improvements**: Share the current SKILL.md and  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m describe what you observed. Ask: "I noticed Claude B forgot to filter test  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m accounts when I asked for a regional report. The Skill mentions filtering,  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m but maybe it's not prominent enough?"                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Review Claude A's suggestions**: Claude A might suggest reorganizing   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m to make rules more prominent, using stronger language like "MUST filter"    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m instead of "always filter", or restructuring the workflow section.          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. **Apply and test changes**: Update the Skill with Claude A's             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m refinements, then test again with Claude B on similar requests              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 6. **Repeat based on usage**: Continue this observe-refine-test cycle as    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m you encounter new scenarios. Each iteration improves the Skill based on     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m real agent behavior, not assumptions.                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Gathering team feedback:**                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Share Skills with teammates and observe their usage                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Ask: Does the Skill activate when expected? Are instructions clear?      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m What's missing?                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Incorporate feedback to address blind spots in your own usage patterns   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Why this approach works**: Claude A understands agent needs, you provide  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m domain expertise, Claude B reveals gaps through real usage, and iterative   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m refinement improves Skills based on observed behavior rather than           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m assumptions.                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Observe how Claude navigates Skills                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m As you iterate on Skills, pay attention to how Claude actually uses them in [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m practice. Watch for:                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Unexpected exploration paths**: Does Claude read files in an order you  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m didn't anticipate? This might indicate your structure isn't as intuitive as [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m you thought                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Missed connections**: Does Claude fail to follow references to          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m important files? Your links might need to be more explicit or prominent     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Overreliance on certain sections**: If Claude repeatedly reads the same [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m file, consider whether that content should be in the main SKILL.md instead  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Ignored content**: If Claude never accesses a bundled file, it might be [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m unnecessary or poorly signaled in the main instructions                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Iterate based on these observations rather than assumptions. The 'name' and [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 'description' in your Skill's metadata are particularly critical. Claude    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m uses these when deciding whether to trigger the Skill in response to the    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m current task. Make sure they clearly describe what the Skill does and when  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m it should be used.                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Anti-patterns to avoid                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Avoid Windows-style paths                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Always use forward slashes in file paths, even on Windows:                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * ✓ **Good**: `scripts/helper.py`, `reference/guide.md`                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * ✗ **Avoid**: `scripts\helper.py`, `reference\guide.md`                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Unix-style paths work across all platforms, while Windows-style paths cause [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m errors on Unix systems.                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Avoid offering too many options                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Don't present multiple approaches unless necessary:                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad example: Too many choices** (confusing):                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "You can use pypdf, or pdfplumber, or PyMuPDF, or pdf2image, or..."         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good example: Provide a default** (with escape hatch):                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "Use pdfplumber for text extraction:                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m import pdfplumber                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For scanned PDFs requiring OCR, use pdf2image with pytesseract instead."    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Advanced: Skills with executable code                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The sections below focus on Skills that include executable scripts. If your [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Skill uses only markdown instructions, skip to [Checklist for effective     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Skills](#checklist-for-effective-skills).                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Solve, don't punt                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When writing scripts for Skills, handle error conditions rather than        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m punting to Claude.                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good example: Handle errors explicitly**:                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python  theme={null}                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m def process_file(path):                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     """Process a file, creating it if it doesn't exist."""                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     try:                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         with open(path) as f:                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             return f.read()                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     except FileNotFoundError:                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         # Create file with default content instead of failing               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         print(f"File {path} not found, creating default")                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         with open(path, 'w') as f:                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m             f.write('')                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         return ''                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     except PermissionError:                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         # Provide alternative instead of failing                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         print(f"Cannot access {path}, using default")                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m         return ''                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad example: Punt to Claude**:                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python  theme={null}                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m def process_file(path):                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     # Just fail and let Claude figure it out                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     return open(path).read()                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Configuration parameters should also be justified and documented to avoid   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "voodoo constants" (Ousterhout's law). If you don't know the right value,   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m how will Claude determine it?                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good example: Self-documenting**:                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python  theme={null}                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # HTTP requests typically complete within 30 seconds                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Longer timeout accounts for slow connections                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m REQUEST_TIMEOUT = 30                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Three retries balances reliability vs speed                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Most intermittent failures resolve by the second retry                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m MAX_RETRIES = 3                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad example: Magic numbers**:                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python  theme={null}                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m TIMEOUT = 47  # Why 47?                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m RETRIES = 5   # Why 5?                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Provide utility scripts                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Even if Claude could write a script, pre-made scripts offer advantages:     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Benefits of utility scripts**:                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * More reliable than generated code                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Save tokens (no need to include code in context)                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Save time (no code generation required)                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * Ensure consistency across uses                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <img                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m src="https://mintcdn.com/anthropic-claude-docs/4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00/images/agen [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m t-skills-executable-scripts.png?fit=max&auto=format&n=4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00&q=85 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m &s=4bbc45f2c2e0bee9f2f0d5da669bad00" alt="Bundling executable scripts       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m alongside instruction files" data-og-width="2048" width="2048"              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m data-og-height="1154" height="1154"                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m data-path="images/agent-skills-executable-scripts.png" data-optimize="true" [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m data-opv="3"                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m srcset="https://mintcdn.com/anthropic-claude-docs/4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00/images/a [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m gent-skills-executable-scripts.png?w=280&fit=max&auto=format&n=4Bny2bjzuGBK [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 7o00&q=85&s=9a04e6535a8467bfeea492e517de389f 280w,                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m https://mintcdn.com/anthropic-claude-docs/4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00/images/agent-ski [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m lls-executable-scripts.png?w=560&fit=max&auto=format&n=4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00&q=8 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5&s=e49333ad90141af17c0d7651cca7216b 560w,                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m https://mintcdn.com/anthropic-claude-docs/4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00/images/agent-ski [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m lls-executable-scripts.png?w=840&fit=max&auto=format&n=4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00&q=8 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5&s=954265a5df52223d6572b6214168c428 840w,                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m https://mintcdn.com/anthropic-claude-docs/4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00/images/agent-ski [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m lls-executable-scripts.png?w=1100&fit=max&auto=format&n=4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00&q= [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 85&s=2ff7a2d8f2a83ee8af132b29f10150fd 1100w,                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m https://mintcdn.com/anthropic-claude-docs/4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00/images/agent-ski [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m lls-executable-scripts.png?w=1650&fit=max&auto=format&n=4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00&q= [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 85&s=48ab96245e04077f4d15e9170e081cfb 1650w,                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m https://mintcdn.com/anthropic-claude-docs/4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00/images/agent-ski [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m lls-executable-scripts.png?w=2500&fit=max&auto=format&n=4Bny2bjzuGBK7o00&q= [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 85&s=0301a6c8b3ee879497cc5b5483177c90 2500w" />                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The diagram above shows how executable scripts work alongside instruction   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m files. The instruction file (forms.md) references the script, and Claude    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m can execute it without loading its contents into context.                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Important distinction**: Make clear in your instructions whether Claude   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m should:                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Execute the script** (most common): "Run `analyze_form.py` to extract   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fields"                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Read it as reference** (for complex logic): "See `analyze_form.py` for  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the field extraction algorithm"                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For most utility scripts, execution is preferred because it's more reliable [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and efficient. See the [Runtime environment](#runtime-environment) section  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m below for details on how script execution works.                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example**:                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Utility scripts                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **analyze_form.py**: Extract all form fields from PDF                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m python scripts/analyze_form.py input.pdf > fields.json                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Output format:                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```json                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m {                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   "field_name": {"type": "text", "x": 100, "y": 200},                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   "signature": {"type": "sig", "x": 150, "y": 500}                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m }                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **validate_boxes.py**: Check for overlapping bounding boxes                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m python scripts/validate_boxes.py fields.json                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Returns: "OK" or lists conflicts                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **fill_form.py**: Apply field values to PDF                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m python scripts/fill_form.py input.pdf fields.json output.pdf                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Use visual analysis                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When inputs can be rendered as images, have Claude analyze them:            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Form layout analysis                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Convert PDF to images:                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```powershell                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    python scripts/pdf_to_images.py form.pdf                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    ```                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Analyze each page image to identify form fields                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Claude can see field locations and types visually                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <Note>                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   In this example, you'd need to write the `pdf_to_images.py` script.       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </Note>                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude's vision capabilities help understand layouts and structures.        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Create verifiable intermediate outputs                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When Claude performs complex, open-ended tasks, it can make mistakes. The   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "plan-validate-execute" pattern catches errors early by having Claude first [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m create a plan in a structured format, then validate that plan with a script [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m before executing it.                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example**: Imagine asking Claude to update 50 form fields in a PDF based  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m on a spreadsheet. Without validation, Claude might reference non-existent   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fields, create conflicting values, miss required fields, or apply updates   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m incorrectly.                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Solution**: Use the workflow pattern shown above (PDF form filling), but  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m add an intermediate `changes.json` file that gets validated before applying [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m changes. The workflow becomes: analyze → **create plan file** → **validate  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m plan** → execute → verify.                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Why this pattern works:**                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Catches errors early**: Validation finds problems before changes are    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m applied                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Machine-verifiable**: Scripts provide objective verification            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Reversible planning**: Claude can iterate on the plan without touching  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m originals                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Clear debugging**: Error messages point to specific problems            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to use**: Batch operations, destructive changes, complex validation  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m rules, high-stakes operations.                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Implementation tip**: Make validation scripts verbose with specific error [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m messages like "Field 'signature\_date' not found. Available fields:         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m customer\_name, order\_total, signature\_date\_signed" to help Claude fix   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m issues.                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Package dependencies                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Skills run in the code execution environment with platform-specific         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m limitations:                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **claude.ai**: Can install packages from npm and PyPI and pull from       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m GitHub repositories                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Anthropic API**: Has no network access and no runtime package           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m installation                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m List required packages in your SKILL.md and verify they're available in the [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [code execution tool                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m documentation](/en/docs/agents-and-tools/tool-use/code-execution-tool).     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Runtime environment                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Skills run in a code execution environment with filesystem access,          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m powershell commands, and code execution capabilities. For the conceptual    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m explanation of this architecture, see [The Skills                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m architecture](/en/docs/agents-and-tools/agent-skills/overview#the-skills-ar [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m chitecture) in the overview.                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How this affects your authoring:**                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How Claude accesses Skills:**                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Metadata pre-loaded**: At startup, the name and description from all   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Skills' YAML frontmatter are loaded into the system prompt                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Files read on-demand**: Claude uses powershell Read tools to access    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m SKILL.md and other files from the filesystem when needed                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Scripts executed efficiently**: Utility scripts can be executed via    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m powershell without loading their full contents into context. Only the       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m script's output consumes tokens                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **No context penalty for large files**: Reference files, data, or        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m documentation don't consume context tokens until actually read              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **File paths matter**: Claude navigates your skill directory like a       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m filesystem. Use forward slashes (`reference/guide.md`), not backslashes     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Name files descriptively**: Use names that indicate content:            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `form_validation_rules.md`, not `doc2.md`                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Organize for discovery**: Structure directories by domain or feature    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   * Good: `reference/finance.md`, `reference/sales.md`                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   * Bad: `docs/file1.md`, `docs/file2.md`                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Bundle comprehensive resources**: Include complete API docs, extensive  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m examples, large datasets; no context penalty until accessed                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Prefer scripts for deterministic operations**: Write `validate_form.py` [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m rather than asking Claude to generate validation code                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Make execution intent clear**:                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   * "Run `analyze_form.py` to extract fields" (execute)                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m   * "See `analyze_form.py` for the extraction algorithm" (read as           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m reference)                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * **Test file access patterns**: Verify Claude can navigate your directory  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m structure by testing with real requests                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m bigquery-skill/                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ├── SKILL.md (overview, points to reference files)                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m └── reference/                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ├── finance.md (revenue metrics)                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     ├── sales.md (pipeline data)                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m     └── product.md (usage analytics)                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When the user asks about revenue, Claude reads SKILL.md, sees the reference [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m to `reference/finance.md`, and invokes powershell to read just that file.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The sales.md and product.md files remain on the filesystem, consuming zero  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m context tokens until needed. This filesystem-based model is what enables    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m progressive disclosure. Claude can navigate and selectively load exactly    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m what each task requires.                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For complete details on the technical architecture, see [How Skills         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m work](/en/docs/agents-and-tools/agent-skills/overview#how-skills-work) in   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the Skills overview.                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### MCP tool references                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If your Skill uses MCP (Model Context Protocol) tools, always use fully     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m qualified tool names to avoid "tool not found" errors.                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Format**: `ServerName:tool_name`                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example**:                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown  theme={null}                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use the BigQuery:bigquery_schema tool to retrieve table schemas.            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Use the GitHub:create_issue tool to create issues.                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Where:                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * `BigQuery` and `GitHub` are MCP server names                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * `bigquery_schema` and `create_issue` are the tool names within those      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m servers                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Without the server prefix, Claude may fail to locate the tool, especially   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m when multiple MCP servers are available.                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Avoid assuming tools are installed                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Don't assume packages are available:                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````markdown  theme={null}                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad example: Assumes installation**:                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "Use the pdf library to process the file."                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good example: Explicit about dependencies**:                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "Install required package: `pip install pypdf`                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Then use it:                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```python                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m from pypdf import PdfReader                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m reader = PdfReader("file.pdf")                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```"                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ````                                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Technical notes                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### YAML frontmatter requirements                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The SKILL.md frontmatter requires `name` (64 characters max) and            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `description` (1024 characters max) fields. See the [Skills                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m overview](/en/docs/agents-and-tools/agent-skills/overview#skill-structure)  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m for complete structure details.                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Token budgets                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Keep SKILL.md body under 500 lines for optimal performance. If your content [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m exceeds this, split it into separate files using the progressive disclosure [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m patterns described earlier. For architectural details, see the [Skills      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m overview](/en/docs/agents-and-tools/agent-skills/overview#how-skills-work). [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Checklist for effective Skills                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Before sharing a Skill, verify:                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Core quality                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Description is specific and includes key terms                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Description includes both what the Skill does and when to use it      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] SKILL.md body is under 500 lines                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Additional details are in separate files (if needed)                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] No time-sensitive information (or in "old patterns" section)          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Consistent terminology throughout                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Examples are concrete, not abstract                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] File references are one level deep                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Progressive disclosure used appropriately                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Workflows have clear steps                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Code and scripts                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Scripts solve problems rather than punt to Claude                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Error handling is explicit and helpful                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] No "voodoo constants" (all values justified)                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Required packages listed in instructions and verified as available    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Scripts have clear documentation                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] No Windows-style paths (all forward slashes)                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Validation/verification steps for critical operations                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Feedback loops included for quality-critical tasks                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Testing                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] At least three evaluations created                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Tested with Haiku, Sonnet, and Opus                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Tested with real usage scenarios                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m * [ ] Team feedback incorporated (if applicable)                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
