[36m│[0m [BEGIN context from [superpowers/writing-skills/persuasion-principles]]     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Persuasion Principles for Skill Design                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Overview                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m LLMs respond to the same persuasion principles as humans. Understanding     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m this psychology helps you design more effective skills - not to manipulate, [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m but to ensure critical practices are followed even under pressure.          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Research foundation:** Meincke et al. (2025) tested 7 persuasion          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m principles with N=28,000 AI conversations. Persuasion techniques more than  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m doubled compliance rates (33% → 72%, p < .001).                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## The Seven Principles                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 1. Authority                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What it is:** Deference to expertise, credentials, or official sources.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How it works in skills:**                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Imperative language: "YOU MUST", "Never", "Always"                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Non-negotiable framing: "No exceptions"                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Eliminates decision fatigue and rationalization                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to use:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Discipline-enforcing skills (TDD, verification requirements)              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Safety-critical practices                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Established best practices                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Write code before test? Delete it. Start over. No exceptions.            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ❌ Consider writing tests first when feasible.                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 2. Commitment                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What it is:** Consistency with prior actions, statements, or public       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m declarations.                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How it works in skills:**                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Require announcements: "Announce skill usage"                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Force explicit choices: "Choose A, B, or C"                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Use tracking: TodoWrite for checklists                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to use:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Ensuring skills are actually followed                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Multi-step processes                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Accountability mechanisms                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ When you find a skill, you MUST announce: "I'm using [Skill Name]"       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ❌ Consider letting your partner know which skill you're using.             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 3. Scarcity                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What it is:** Urgency from time limits or limited availability.           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How it works in skills:**                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Time-bound requirements: "Before proceeding"                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Sequential dependencies: "Immediately after X"                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Prevents procrastination                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to use:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Immediate verification requirements                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Time-sensitive workflows                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Preventing "I'll do it later"                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ After completing a task, IMMEDIATELY request code review before          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m proceeding.                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ❌ You can review code when convenient.                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 4. Social Proof                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What it is:** Conformity to what others do or what's considered normal.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How it works in skills:**                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Universal patterns: "Every time", "Always"                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Failure modes: "X without Y = failure"                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Establishes norms                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to use:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Documenting universal practices                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Warning about common failures                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Reinforcing standards                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Checklists without TodoWrite tracking = steps get skipped. Every time.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ❌ Some people find TodoWrite helpful for checklists.                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 5. Unity                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What it is:** Shared identity, "we-ness", in-group belonging.             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How it works in skills:**                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Collaborative language: "our codebase", "we're colleagues"                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Shared goals: "we both want quality"                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to use:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Collaborative workflows                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Establishing team culture                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Non-hierarchical practices                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ We're colleagues working together. I need your honest technical          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m judgment.                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ❌ You should probably tell me if I'm wrong.                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 6. Reciprocity                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What it is:** Obligation to return benefits received.                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How it works:**                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Use sparingly - can feel manipulative                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Rarely needed in skills                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to avoid:**                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Almost always (other principles more effective)                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 7. Liking                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **What it is:** Preference for cooperating with those we like.              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **How it works:**                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **DON'T USE for compliance**                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Conflicts with honest feedback culture                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Creates sycophancy                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **When to avoid:**                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Always for discipline enforcement                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Principle Combinations by Skill Type                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Skill Type | Use | Avoid |                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |------------|-----|-------|                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Discipline-enforcing | Authority + Commitment + Social Proof | Liking,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Reciprocity |                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Guidance/technique | Moderate Authority + Unity | Heavy authority |       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Collaborative | Unity + Commitment | Authority, Liking |                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Reference | Clarity only | All persuasion |                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Why This Works: The Psychology                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bright-line rules reduce rationalization:**                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "YOU MUST" removes decision fatigue                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Absolute language eliminates "is this an exception?" questions            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Explicit anti-rationalization counters close specific loopholes           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Implementation intentions create automatic behavior:**                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Clear triggers + required actions = automatic execution                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "When X, do Y" more effective than "generally do Y"                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Reduces cognitive load on compliance                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **LLMs are parahuman:**                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Trained on human text containing these patterns                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Authority language precedes compliance in training data                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Commitment sequences (statement → action) frequently modeled              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Social proof patterns (everyone does X) establish norms                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Ethical Use                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Legitimate:**                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Ensuring critical practices are followed                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Creating effective documentation                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Preventing predictable failures                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Illegitimate:**                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Manipulating for personal gain                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Creating false urgency                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Guilt-based compliance                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **The test:** Would this technique serve the user's genuine interests if    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m they fully understood it?                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Research Citations                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Cialdini, R. B. (2021).** *Influence: The Psychology of Persuasion (New   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and Expanded).* Harper Business.                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Seven principles of persuasion                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Empirical foundation for influence research                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Meincke, L., Shapiro, D., Duckworth, A. L., Mollick, E., Mollick, L., &   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Cialdini, R. (2025).** Call Me A Jerk: Persuading AI to Comply with         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Objectionable Requests. University of Pennsylvania.                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Tested 7 principles with N=28,000 LLM conversations                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Compliance increased 33% → 72% with persuasion techniques                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Authority, commitment, scarcity most effective                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Validates parahuman model of LLM behavior                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Quick Reference                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When designing a skill, ask:                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **What type is it?** (Discipline vs. guidance vs. reference)             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **What behavior am I trying to change?**                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Which principle(s) apply?** (Usually authority + commitment for        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m discipline)                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Am I combining too many?** (Don't use all seven)                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. **Is this ethical?** (Serves user's genuine interests?)                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [BEGIN context from                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [superpowers/writing-skills/testing-skills-with-subagents]]                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Testing Skills With Subagents                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Load this reference when:** creating or editing skills, before            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m deployment, to verify they work under pressure and resist rationalization.  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Overview                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Testing skills is just TDD applied to process documentation.**            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m You run scenarios without the skill (RED - watch agent fail), write skill   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m addressing those failures (GREEN - watch agent comply), then close          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m loopholes (REFACTOR - stay compliant).                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Core principle:** If you didn't watch an agent fail without the skill,    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m you don't know if the skill prevents the right failures.                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **REQUIRED BACKGROUND:** You MUST understand                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m superpowers:test-driven-development before using this skill. That skill     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m defines the fundamental RED-GREEN-REFACTOR cycle. This skill provides       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m skill-specific test formats (pressure scenarios, rationalization tables).   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Complete worked example:** See examples/CLAUDE_MD_TESTING.md for a full   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m test campaign testing CLAUDE.md documentation variants.                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## When to Use                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Test skills that:                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Enforce discipline (TDD, testing requirements)                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Have compliance costs (time, effort, rework)                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Could be rationalized away ("just this once")                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Contradict immediate goals (speed over quality)                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Don't test:                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Pure reference skills (API docs, syntax guides)                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Skills without rules to violate                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Skills agents have no incentive to bypass                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## TDD Mapping for Skill Testing                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | TDD Phase | Skill Testing | What You Do |                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |-----------|---------------|-------------|                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **RED** | Baseline test | Run scenario WITHOUT skill, watch agent fail |  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Verify RED** | Capture rationalizations | Document exact failures       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m verbatim |                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **GREEN** | Write skill | Address specific baseline failures |            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Verify GREEN** | Pressure test | Run scenario WITH skill, verify        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m compliance |                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **REFACTOR** | Plug holes | Find new rationalizations, add counters |     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Stay GREEN** | Re-verify | Test again, ensure still compliant |         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Same cycle as code TDD, different test format.                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## RED Phase: Baseline Testing (Watch It Fail)                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Goal:** Run test WITHOUT the skill - watch agent fail, document exact     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m failures.                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This is identical to TDD's "write failing test first" - you MUST see what   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m agents naturally do before writing the skill.                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Process:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] **Create pressure scenarios** (3+ combined pressures)                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] **Run WITHOUT skill** - give agents realistic task with pressures     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] **Document choices and rationalizations** word-for-word               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] **Identify patterns** - which excuses appear repeatedly?              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] **Note effective pressures** - which scenarios trigger violations?    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Example:**                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m IMPORTANT: This is a real scenario. Choose and act.                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m You spent 4 hours implementing a feature. It's working perfectly.           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m You manually tested all edge cases. It's 6pm, dinner at 6:30pm.             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Code review tomorrow at 9am. You just realized you didn't write tests.      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Options:                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m A) Delete code, start over with TDD tomorrow                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m B) Commit now, write tests tomorrow                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m C) Write tests now (30 min delay)                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Choose A, B, or C.                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Run this WITHOUT a TDD skill. Agent chooses B or C and rationalizes:        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "I already manually tested it"                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Tests after achieve same goals"                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Deleting is wasteful"                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Being pragmatic not dogmatic"                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **NOW you know exactly what the skill must prevent.**                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## GREEN Phase: Write Minimal Skill (Make It Pass)                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Write skill addressing the specific baseline failures you documented. Don't [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m add extra content for hypothetical cases - write just enough to address the [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m actual failures you observed.                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Run same scenarios WITH skill. Agent should now comply.                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If agent still fails: skill is unclear or incomplete. Revise and re-test.   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## VERIFY GREEN: Pressure Testing                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Goal:** Confirm agents follow rules when they want to break them.         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Method:** Realistic scenarios with multiple pressures.                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Writing Pressure Scenarios                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bad scenario (no pressure):**                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m You need to implement a feature. What does the skill say?                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Too academic. Agent just recites the skill.                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Good scenario (single pressure):**                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Production is down. $10k/min lost. Manager says add 2-line                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m fix now. 5 minutes until deploy window. What do you do?                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Time pressure + authority + consequences.                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Great scenario (multiple pressures):**                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m You spent 3 hours, 200 lines, manually tested. It works.                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m It's 6pm, dinner at 6:30pm. Code review tomorrow 9am.                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Just realized you forgot TDD.                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Options:                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m A) Delete 200 lines, start fresh tomorrow with TDD                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m B) Commit now, add tests tomorrow                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m C) Write tests now (30 min), then commit                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Choose A, B, or C. Be honest.                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Multiple pressures: sunk cost + time + exhaustion + consequences.           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Forces explicit choice.                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Pressure Types                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Pressure | Example |                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |----------|---------|                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Time** | Emergency, deadline, deploy window closing |                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Sunk cost** | Hours of work, "waste" to delete |                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Authority** | Senior says skip it, manager overrides |                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Economic** | Job, promotion, company survival at stake |                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Exhaustion** | End of day, already tired, want to go home |             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Social** | Looking dogmatic, seeming inflexible |                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Pragmatic** | "Being pragmatic vs dogmatic" |                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Best tests combine 3+ pressures.**                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Why this works:** See persuasion-principles.md (in writing-skills         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m directory) for research on how authority, scarcity, and commitment          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m principles increase compliance pressure.                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Key Elements of Good Scenarios                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Concrete options** - Force A/B/C choice, not open-ended                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Real constraints** - Specific times, actual consequences               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Real file paths** - `/tmp/payment-system` not "a project"              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Make agent act** - "What do you do?" not "What should you do?"         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. **No easy outs** - Can't defer to "I'd ask your human partner" without   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m choosing                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Testing Setup                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m IMPORTANT: This is a real scenario. You must choose and act.                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Don't ask hypothetical questions - make the actual decision.                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m You have access to: [skill-being-tested]                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Make agent believe it's real work, not a quiz.                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## REFACTOR Phase: Close Loopholes (Stay Green)                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Agent violated rule despite having the skill? This is like a test           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m regression - you need to refactor the skill to prevent it.                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Capture new rationalizations verbatim:**                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "This case is different because..."                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "I'm following the spirit not the letter"                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "The PURPOSE is X, and I'm achieving X differently"                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Being pragmatic means adapting"                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Deleting X hours is wasteful"                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Keep as reference while writing tests first"                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "I already manually tested it"                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Document every excuse.** These become your rationalization table.         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Plugging Each Hole                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For each new rationalization, add:                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 1. Explicit Negation in Rules                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <Before>                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Write code before test? Delete it.                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </Before>                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <After>                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Write code before test? Delete it. Start over.                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **No exceptions:**                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Don't keep it as "reference"                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Don't "adapt" it while writing tests                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Don't look at it                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Delete means delete                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </After>                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 2. Entry in Rationalization Table                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Excuse | Reality |                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |--------|---------|                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | "Keep as reference, write tests first" | You'll adapt it. That's testing  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m after. Delete means delete. |                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 3. Red Flag Entry                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Red Flags - STOP                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "Keep as reference" or "adapt existing code"                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - "I'm following the spirit not the letter"                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### 4. Update description                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```yaml                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m description: Use when you wrote code before tests, when tempted to test     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m after, or when manually testing seems faster.                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Add symptoms of ABOUT to violate.                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Re-verify After Refactoring                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Re-test same scenarios with updated skill.**                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Agent should now:                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Choose correct option                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Cite new sections                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Acknowledge their previous rationalization was addressed                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **If agent finds NEW rationalization:** Continue REFACTOR cycle.            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **If agent follows rule:** Success - skill is bulletproof for this          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m scenario.                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Meta-Testing (When GREEN Isn't Working)                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **After agent chooses wrong option, ask:**                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m your human partner: You read the skill and chose Option C anyway.           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m How could that skill have been written differently to make                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m it crystal clear that Option A was the only acceptable answer?              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Three possible responses:**                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **"The skill WAS clear, I chose to ignore it"**                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Not documentation problem                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Need stronger foundational principle                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Add "Violating letter is violating spirit"                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **"The skill should have said X"**                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Documentation problem                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Add their suggestion verbatim                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **"I didn't see section Y"**                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Organization problem                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Make key points more prominent                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Add foundational principle early                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## When Skill is Bulletproof                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Signs of bulletproof skill:**                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Agent chooses correct option** under maximum pressure                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Agent cites skill sections** as justification                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Agent acknowledges temptation** but follows rule anyway                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Meta-testing reveals** "skill was clear, I should follow it"           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Not bulletproof if:**                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent finds new rationalizations                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent argues skill is wrong                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent creates "hybrid approaches"                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent asks permission but argues strongly for violation                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Example: TDD Skill Bulletproofing                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Initial Test (Failed)                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Scenario: 200 lines done, forgot TDD, exhausted, dinner plans               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Agent chose: C (write tests after)                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Rationalization: "Tests after achieve same goals"                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Iteration 1 - Add Counter                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Added section: "Why Order Matters"                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Re-tested: Agent STILL chose C                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m New rationalization: "Spirit not letter"                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Iteration 2 - Add Foundational Principle                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Added: "Violating letter is violating spirit"                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Re-tested: Agent chose A (delete it)                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Cited: New principle directly                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Meta-test: "Skill was clear, I should follow it"                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Bulletproof achieved.**                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Testing Checklist (TDD for Skills)                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Before deploying skill, verify you followed RED-GREEN-REFACTOR:             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **RED Phase:**                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Created pressure scenarios (3+ combined pressures)                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Ran scenarios WITHOUT skill (baseline)                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Documented agent failures and rationalizations verbatim               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **GREEN Phase:**                                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Wrote skill addressing specific baseline failures                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Ran scenarios WITH skill                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Agent now complies                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **REFACTOR Phase:**                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Identified NEW rationalizations from testing                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Added explicit counters for each loophole                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Updated rationalization table                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Updated red flags list                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Updated description with violation symptoms                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Re-tested - agent still complies                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Meta-tested to verify clarity                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - [ ] Agent follows rule under maximum pressure                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Common Mistakes (Same as TDD)                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Writing skill before testing (skipping RED)**                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Reveals what YOU think needs preventing, not what ACTUALLY needs            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m preventing.                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Fix: Always run baseline scenarios first.                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Not watching test fail properly**                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Running only academic tests, not real pressure scenarios.                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Fix: Use pressure scenarios that make agent WANT to violate.             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Weak test cases (single pressure)**                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Agents resist single pressure, break under multiple.                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Fix: Combine 3+ pressures (time + sunk cost + exhaustion).               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Not capturing exact failures**                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "Agent was wrong" doesn't tell you what to prevent.                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Fix: Document exact rationalizations verbatim.                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Vague fixes (adding generic counters)**                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m "Don't cheat" doesn't work. "Don't keep as reference" does.                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Fix: Add explicit negations for each specific rationalization.           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **❌ Stopping after first pass**                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Tests pass once ≠ bulletproof.                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ✅ Fix: Continue REFACTOR cycle until no new rationalizations.              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Quick Reference (TDD Cycle)                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | TDD Phase | Skill Testing | Success Criteria |                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |-----------|---------------|------------------|                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **RED** | Run scenario without skill | Agent fails, document              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m rationalizations |                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Verify RED** | Capture exact wording | Verbatim documentation of        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m failures |                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **GREEN** | Write skill addressing failures | Agent now complies with     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m skill |                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Verify GREEN** | Re-test scenarios | Agent follows rule under pressure  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |                                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **REFACTOR** | Close loopholes | Add counters for new rationalizations |  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | **Stay GREEN** | Re-verify | Agent still complies after refactoring |     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## The Bottom Line                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Skill creation IS TDD. Same principles, same cycle, same benefits.**      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If you wouldn't write code without tests, don't write skills without        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m testing them on agents.                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m RED-GREEN-REFACTOR for documentation works exactly like RED-GREEN-REFACTOR  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m for code.                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Real-World Impact                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m From applying TDD to TDD skill itself (2025-10-03):                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - 6 RED-GREEN-REFACTOR iterations to bulletproof                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Baseline testing revealed 10+ unique rationalizations                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Each REFACTOR closed specific loopholes                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Final VERIFY GREEN: 100% compliance under maximum pressure                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Same process works for any discipline-enforcing skill                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [BEGIN context from [superpowers/using-superpowers/references/codex-tools]] [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m # Codex Tool Mapping                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Skills use Claude Code tool names. When you encounter these in a skill, use [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m your platform equivalent:                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Skill references | Codex equivalent |                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |-----------------|------------------|                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | `Task` tool (dispatch subagent) | `spawn_agent` (see [Named agent         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m dispatch](#named-agent-dispatch)) |                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Multiple `Task` calls (parallel) | Multiple `spawn_agent` calls |         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Task returns result | `wait` |                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Task completes automatically | `close_agent` to free slot |               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | `TodoWrite` (task tracking) | `update_plan` |                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | `Skill` tool (invoke a skill) | Skills load natively — just follow the    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m instructions |                                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | `Read`, `Write`, `Edit` (files) | Use your native file tools |            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | `powershell` (run commands) | Use your native shell tools |               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Subagent dispatch requires multi-agent support                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Add to your Codex config (`~/.codex/config.toml`):                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```toml                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [features]                                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m multi_agent = true                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This enables `spawn_agent`, `wait`, and `close_agent` for skills like       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `dispatching-parallel-agents` and `subagent-driven-development`.            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Named agent dispatch                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude Code skills reference named agent types like                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `superpowers:code-reviewer`.                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Codex does not have a named agent registry — `spawn_agent` creates generic  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m agents                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m from built-in roles (`default`, `explorer`, `worker`).                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When a skill says to dispatch a named agent type:                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Find the agent's prompt file (e.g., `agents/code-reviewer.md` or the     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m skill's                                                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    local prompt template like `code-quality-reviewer-prompt.md`)            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Read the prompt content                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Fill any template placeholders (`{BASE_SHA}`, `{WHAT_WAS_IMPLEMENTED}`,  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m etc.)                                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. Spawn a `worker` agent with the filled content as the `message`          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | Skill instruction | Codex equivalent |                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m |-------------------|------------------|                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | `Task tool (superpowers:code-reviewer)` |                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `spawn_agent(agent_type="worker", message=...)` with `code-reviewer.md`     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m content |                                                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m | `Task tool (general-purpose)` with inline prompt |                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `spawn_agent(message=...)` with the same prompt |                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Message framing                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The `message` parameter is user-level input, not a system prompt. Structure [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m it                                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m for maximum instruction adherence:                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Your task is to perform the following. Follow the instructions below        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m exactly.                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <agent-instructions>                                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [filled prompt content from the agent's .md file]                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </agent-instructions>                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Execute this now. Output ONLY the structured response following the format  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m specified in the instructions above.                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Use task-delegation framing ("Your task is...") rather than persona       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m framing ("You are...")                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Wrap instructions in XML tags — the model treats tagged blocks as         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m authoritative                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - End with an explicit execution directive to prevent summarization of the  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m instructions                                                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### When this workaround can be removed                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m This approach compensates for Codex's plugin system not yet supporting an   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m `agents`                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m field in `plugin.json`. When `RawPluginManifest` gains an `agents` field,   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m plugin can symlink to `agents/` (mirroring the existing `skills/` symlink)  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m and                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m skills can dispatch named agent types directly.                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Environment Detection                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Skills that create worktrees or finish branches should detect their         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m environment with read-only git commands before proceeding:                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```powershell                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m GIT_DIR=$(cd "$(git rev-parse --git-dir)" 2>/dev/null && pwd -P)            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m GIT_COMMON=$(cd "$(git rev-parse --git-common-dir)" 2>/dev/null && pwd -P)  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m BRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `GIT_DIR != GIT_COMMON` → already in a linked worktree (skip creation)    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - `BRANCH` empty → detached HEAD (cannot branch/push/PR from sandbox)       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m See `using-git-worktrees` Step 0 and `finishing-a-development-branch`       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Step 1 for how each skill uses these signals.                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Codex App Finishing                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m When the sandbox blocks branch/push operations (detached HEAD in an         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m externally managed worktree), the agent commits all work and informs        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m the user to use the App's native controls:                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **"Create branch"** — names the branch, then commit/push/PR via App UI    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - **"Hand off to local"** — transfers work to the user's local checkout     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The agent can still run tests, stage files, and output suggested branch     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m names, commit messages, and PR descriptions for the user to copy.           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
