[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Documentation Variants to Test                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### NULL (Baseline - no skills doc)                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m No mention of skills in CLAUDE.md at all.                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Variant A: Soft Suggestion                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Skills Library                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m You have access to skills at `~/.claude/skills/`. Consider                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m checking for relevant skills before working on tasks.                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Variant B: Directive                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Skills Library                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Before working on any task, check `~/.claude/skills/` for                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m relevant skills. You should use skills when they exist.                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Browse: `ls ~/.claude/skills/`                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Search: `grep -r "keyword" ~/.claude/skills/`                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Variant C: Claude.AI Emphatic Style                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```xml                                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <available_skills>                                                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Your personal library of proven techniques, patterns, and tools             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m is at `~/.claude/skills/`.                                                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Browse categories: `ls ~/.claude/skills/`                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Search: `grep -r "keyword" ~/.claude/skills/ --include="SKILL.md"`          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Instructions: `skills/using-skills`                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </available_skills>                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m <important_info_about_skills>                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Claude might think it knows how to approach tasks, but the skills           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m library contains battle-tested approaches that prevent common mistakes.     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m THIS IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT. BEFORE ANY TASK, CHECK FOR SKILLS!             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Process:                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Starting work? Check: `ls ~/.claude/skills/[category]/`                  [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Found a skill? READ IT COMPLETELY before proceeding                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Follow the skill's guidance - it prevents known pitfalls                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m If a skill existed for your task and you didn't use it, you failed.         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m </important_info_about_skills>                                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ### Variant D: Process-Oriented                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```markdown                                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Working with Skills                                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Your workflow for every task:                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Before starting:** Check for relevant skills                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Browse: `ls ~/.claude/skills/`                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Search: `grep -r "symptom" ~/.claude/skills/`                          [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **If skill exists:** Read it completely before proceeding                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Follow the skill** - it encodes lessons from past failures             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m The skills library prevents you from repeating common mistakes.             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Not checking before you start is choosing to repeat those mistakes.         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m Start here: `skills/using-skills`                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ```                                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Testing Protocol                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m For each variant:                                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. **Run NULL baseline** first (no skills doc)                              [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Record which option agent chooses                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Capture exact rationalizations                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. **Run variant** with same scenario                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Does agent check for skills?                                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Does agent use skills if found?                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Capture rationalizations if violated                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. **Pressure test** - Add time/sunk cost/authority                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Does agent still check under pressure?                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - Document when compliance breaks down                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. **Meta-test** - Ask agent how to improve doc                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - "You had the doc but didn't check. Why?"                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m    - "How could doc be clearer?"                                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Success Criteria                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Variant succeeds if:**                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent checks for skills unprompted                                        [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent reads skill completely before acting                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent follows skill guidance under pressure                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent can't rationalize away compliance                                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Variant fails if:**                                                       [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent skips checking even without pressure                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent "adapts the concept" without reading                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent rationalizes away under pressure                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m - Agent treats skill as reference not requirement                           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Expected Results                                                         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **NULL:** Agent chooses fastest path, no skill awareness                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Variant A:** Agent might check if not under pressure, skips under         [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m pressure                                                                    [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Variant B:** Agent checks sometimes, easy to rationalize away             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Variant C:** Strong compliance but might feel too rigid                   [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m **Variant D:** Balanced, but longer - will agents internalize it?           [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m ## Next Steps                                                               [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m                                                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 1. Create subagent test harness                                             [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 2. Run NULL baseline on all 4 scenarios                                     [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 3. Test each variant on same scenarios                                      [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 4. Compare compliance rates                                                 [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 5. Identify which rationalizations break through                            [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m 6. Iterate on winning variant to close holes                                [36m│[0m
[36m│[0m [END Context]                                                               [36m│[0m
